description: With distinct factory-correct colors and the control of a four-speed manual transmission, this 1974 Chevrolet Corvette is a great standout classic.  And as you look closer to the amount of time and work invested in keeping it looking this good, you soon realize its desirability is in the details.

C3 Corvettes have the look of distinction, and so nobody who sees this car in your driveway will question how affordable it really is.  That's especially true since this one was treated to a full professional respray of its factory-correct Silver Mist.  It's a timeless hue that fits in today considering a similar color is in style on many current Mercedes and Audi vehicles.  And speaking of modern looks, we all know '73 as the debut of the urethane front bumpers front.  These gave the C3 an appearance of one long continuous wave, and it made the '74 much more of a designer's work of art. But just because this was a more streamlined car did not mean it skipped out on brightwork.  It just made great features like the Rally wheels, rocker panels, and rear bumper were much more noticeable.

The factory-correct tan interior is a complement to the sophisticate silver.  It has an understated look that gives this American classic an almost European tone.  There has been a solid investment to make sure everything looks original.  You'll love hopping in, grabbing the three-spoke sports steering wheel, and gazing at the deep dual pod speedo and tach as you cruise around in your classic 'Vette.  And it has all the best in comfort from upgraded leather seats, an AM/FM stereo, and cold air conditioning.  This kind of total package means you take out the T-tops and look cool in your classic 'Vette without breaking a sweat.

Under the hood is an interesting motor.  It's a 350 cubic-inch V8, and it's a factory-replacement block installed by Chevy in 1974.  Since that's what this car still carries today, it tells you it has received the same long-term care of a numbers-matching car, but you have a more interesting story and don't have t pay the status-level price.  But beyond its 1970s appearance is a terrific all-around package that includes all the right features â€“ like a four-barrel carburetor for power, and a new aluminum radiator for reliability.  It has a great throttle response, and you get complete control over this V8 with the desirable four-speed manual transmission.  Add in more driver's features like power steering, four-wheel disc brakes, and the grip of Goodyear Eagle GTII tires, and this is truly an irresistible machine.

When you look beyond terrific color and a loaded interior, you find a great classic with all the best driving features (and we have the build receipts to prove it.)  So at this price, you know this total package 'Vette will not be staying with us long.  Call today!!!
